definitions.definition: make a high-pitched sound or cry.
examples: he oiled the hinges to stop them from squeaking

definitions.definition: say something in a nervous or excited high-pitched tone.
succeed in achieving something by a very narrow margin.
examples: the bill squeaked through with just six votes to spare

definitions.definition: make or have just enough money for basic necessities.
examples: she was squeaking by on her minimum-wage job
